msgid ""
"`getInputStream()`: Locates and opens the resource, returning an "
"`InputStream` for reading from the resource. It is expected that each "
"invocation returns a fresh `InputStream`. It is the responsibility of the "
"caller to close the stream."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/resources.adoc:90
msgid ""
"`exists()`: Returns a `boolean` indicating whether this resource actually "
"exists in physical form."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/resources.adoc:94
msgid ""
"`isOpen()`: Returns a `boolean` indicating whether this resource represents "
"a handle with an open stream. If `true`, the `InputStream` cannot be read "
"multiple times and must be read once only and then closed to avoid resource "
"leaks. Returns `false` for all usual resource implementations, with the "
"exception of `InputStreamResource`."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/resources.adoc:97
msgid ""
"`getDescription()`: Returns a description for this resource, to be used for "
"error output when working with the resource. This is often the fully "
"qualified file name or the actual URL of the resource."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/resources.adoc:101
msgid ""
"Other methods let you obtain an actual `URL` or `File` object representing "
"the resource (if the underlying implementation is compatible and supports "
"that functionality)."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/resources.adoc:105
msgid ""
"Some implementations of the `Resource` interface also implement the extended "
"{spring-framework-api}/core/io/WritableResource.html[`WritableResource`] "
"interface for a resource that supports writing to it."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/resources.adoc:112
msgid ""
"Spring itself uses the `Resource` abstraction extensively, as an argument "
"type in many method signatures when a resource is needed. Other methods in "
"some Spring APIs (such as the constructors to various `ApplicationContext` "
"implementations) take a `String` which in unadorned or simple form is used "
"to create a `Resource` appropriate to that context implementation or, via "
"special prefixes on the `String` path, let the caller specify that a "
"specific `Resource` implementation must be created and used."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/resources.adoc:119
msgid ""
"While the `Resource` interface is used a lot with Spring and by Spring, it "
"is actually very convenient to use as a general utility class by itself in "
"your own code, for access to resources, even when your code does not know or "
"care about any other parts of Spring.  While this couples your code to "
"Spring, it really only couples it to this small set of utility classes, "
"which serves as a more capable replacement for `URL` and can be considered "
"equivalent to any other library you would use for this purpose."
msgstr ""

#. type: Plain text
#: /mnt/c/Users/etrees/Desktop/private/spring-framework/framework-docs/modules/ROOT/pages/core/resources.adoc:122
msgid ""
"The `Resource` abstraction does not replace functionality. It wraps it where "
"possible.  For example, a `UrlResource` wraps a URL and uses the wrapped "
"`URL` to do its work."
msgstr ""

